{
  "intro": {
    "title": "Verbs: Irregular Past Forms",
    "sections": [
      {
        "title": "Regular vs irregular",
        "content": "**Regular verbs** add **-ed** for the past simple and past participle; **irregular verbs** do not — each has its own forms.\nNo rule predicts irregular forms — you must **learn each verb**.",
        "diagrams": [
          {
            "type": "comparison",
            "left": {
              "title": "Regular: + -ed",
              "points": [
                "work → worked",
                "play → played",
                "want → wanted"
              ]
            },
            "right": {
              "title": "Irregular: own forms",
              "points": [
                "go → went → gone",
                "speak → spoke → spoken",
                "write → wrote → written"
              ]
            }
          }
        ],
        "root_ids": [
          "A1.irregular_verbs.basic"
        ],
        "cefr_level": "A1"
      },
      {
        "title": "When you need irregular forms",
        "content": "Irregular forms appear everywhere past forms and participles are needed.",
        "diagrams": [
          {
            "type": "table",
            "title": "Where irregular forms appear",
            "headers": [
              "Structure",
              "Example"
            ],
            "rows": [
              [
                "**Past simple**",
                "I **saw** him yesterday."
              ],
              [
                "**Present/past perfect**",
                "I have **seen** him. She had **written** it."
              ],
              [
                "**Passive**",
                "The letter was **written**. English is **spoken** here."
              ],
              [
                "**Conditionals**",
                "If I had **known**, I would have told you."
              ]
            ]
          }
        ],
        "root_ids": [
          "A1.irregular_verbs.basic"
        ],
        "cefr_level": "A1"
      },
      {
        "title": "Common learner errors",
        "content": "The classic mistake: adding **-ed** to an irregular verb.\nLearn the 50 most common irregular verbs — a full list of forms is in Reference → Irregular verbs.",
        "diagrams": [
          {
            "type": "examples",
            "items": [
              {
                "good": "he **spoke**",
                "bad": "he speaked"
              },
              {
                "good": "I **went**",
                "bad": "I goed"
              },
              {
                "good": "she **wrote**",
                "bad": "she writed"
              },
              {
                "good": "they **made**",
                "bad": "they maked"
              },
              {
                "good": "we **took**",
                "bad": "we taked"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "root_ids": [
          "A1.irregular_verbs.basic"
        ],
        "cefr_level": "A1"
      }
    ]
  },
  "check": {
    "title": "Test your understanding",
    "questions": [
      {
        "type": "mc",
        "question": "He _____ to me yesterday. (speak – past)",
        "options": {
          "a": "speaked",
          "b": "spoke",
          "c": "spoken",
          "d": "speak"
        },
        "correct_option": "b",
        "explanation": "Speak is irregular: speak → spoke → spoken."
      },
      {
        "type": "mc",
        "question": "I _____ to London last year. (go – past)",
        "options": {
          "a": "goed",
          "b": "went",
          "c": "gone",
          "d": "go"
        },
        "correct_option": "b",
        "explanation": "Go is irregular: go → went → gone."
      },
      {
        "type": "mc",
        "question": "She _____ a letter. (write – past)",
        "options": {
          "a": "writed",
          "b": "wrote",
          "c": "written",
          "d": "write"
        },
        "correct_option": "b",
        "explanation": "Write is irregular: write → wrote → written."
      },
      {
        "type": "mc",
        "question": "They _____ a mistake. (make – past)",
        "options": {
          "a": "maked",
          "b": "maded",
          "c": "made",
          "d": "make"
        },
        "correct_option": "c",
        "explanation": "Make is irregular: make → made → made."
      },
      {
        "type": "mc",
        "question": "We _____ him at the party. (see – past)",
        "options": {
          "a": "seed",
          "b": "saw",
          "c": "seen",
          "d": "see"
        },
        "correct_option": "b",
        "explanation": "See is irregular: see → saw → seen."
      }
    ],
    "root_ids": [
      "A2.irregular_verbs.extended"
    ],
    "cefr_level": "A2"
  },
